  [Cambodia](https://www.lexology.com/search/?j=34)
  October 11 2023
  
  
  On 20 September 2023, the Royal Government of Cambodia adopted Sub-Decree No. 286 ANKr.BK on Public Lighting Tax (" **Sub-Decree**"). This Sub-Decree serves to establish a new rate of public lighting tax at 5% (up from the previous 3%) for the supply of alcohol and tobacco products in Cambodia, which is to be effective from 1 January 2024. Rules and procedures for the collection of public lighting tax will be determined by the Ministry of Economy and Finance.
  
